<item>
            <title>[LU-2756] increase OST_BUFSIZE to allow multiple request handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2756</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2424&quot; title=&quot;add memory limits for ptlrpc service&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2424&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2424&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4940&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4940&lt;/a&gt;, the OST_BUFSIZE should be increased to allow for multiple requests to be handled in a single buffer along with a corresponding reduction in OST_NBUFS.  This should only be done for the OST_IO_PORTAL and not the other small request portals.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, if we want to increase the PTLRPC_MAX_BRW_SIZE again, the old OST_BUFSIZE will not be large enough and we have an immediate protocol compatibility problem again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
